Real estate agents are struggling more than ever to convert and the number of contact attempts it takes has increased by literally 10X. 

Here’s what you do: 

Step 1: Create short form videos designed to educate and inform that help build you up as an expert to someone thinking about buying or selling a house. 

PRO TIP: Use FAQs as the content for these videos 

Step 2: [If Possible] Get your past clients to share a 60-second clip of their experience working with you 

Step 3: Advertise these videos to leads as they come into your CRM. Post these videos to FB & IG and then target them as ads to your contacts. 

Step 4: Continue following up.

Leads aren’t as quick to answer the calls and text because they are doing more research on you as a person than ever before socially. By advertising this content directly to them you’re creating a connection that will help you convert more. 👊🏼

Save this post so you can remember the steps. 🛟

But they will spend an enormous amount of time actually looking at property. 

So we leverage the number one thing THEY desire. 🏡

Listen to your consumer, give them what they want, and watch how things shift.

Where’s your area of focus with your client’s wants? ⬇️

Identity. When you change this, you change everything. 👊🏼

My family was going through a bit of a rough patch where it felt like chaos all the time. So, I decided to sit down with everyone and make a shift. 💪🏼

There is a huge difference between having a “command” relationship that uses force to get what you want and relationship that simply inspires change. 

Instead of telling everyone that they needed to quit acting like they were, we all worked together to create a vision of who we wanted to be as the ‘Wise Family’. ❤️

First, we created a T chart. On the left side we listed “who we were” and on the right, “who we were not”. ⚖️

After that we all shared what we had written down. It’s amazing to see what a 5 yr old and a 10 yr old will come up with when you put it down on paper. Brijett and I did the same. 

Then we all thought about the four most important traits we wanted to embody as a family and turned our last name into an acronym and we defined what each of these things meant to us.

👉🏼Winner 
👉🏼Integrity
👉🏼chriSt-like
👉🏼hEalthy 

Each an every day, while we’re eating, we go around the four of us and simply ask each other what we did today to “be” each of these things. 

TALK ABOUT ACCOUNTABILITY. 🙌🏼

I know each and every day that my now 6 yr old, my 10 yr old, and or my wife are going to ask me what I did to be a winner, to have integrity, to be christ-like, and to be healthy. 

What’s amazing to me is how much our family dynamic has changed in such a short period of time. Now, if the kids are acting out of alignment with who we decided we were going to be, we just ask, “Is that what having integrity looks like?” On their own, the kids say yes or no and they adjust their behavior. 🤯

It’s reinforcing this new family identity every single day and we’ll revisit it again after a few months and repeat the exercise to see how we’ll adjust. 

Identity is the one thing you can change that will change everything.

I’m so proud of my family. ❤️

Here are four things I would suggest you do right now to generate new business:

1️⃣- Using listings to get leads
Right now, when inventory is tight, people will search more sources than normal to try and find opportunities for themselves. This means the lead cost is going to be lower than normal and intent will be higher than normal (especially on social). They will turn to more things other than “Zillow” simply because they’ll have seen everything the big Z has to offer.

2️⃣ - Tell Seller Success Stories Constantly
When inventory is low it can be a really good thing for sellers. When demand is high but inventory is low they can typically sell their home for more money in less time than usual. You know that. But your audience might not and they’ll need to be affirmed over and over again to believe it’s possible for them. This isn’t something that you (the person that stands to gain from them selling) can really get them to believe but what Havard calls “third-party validation” can.

Be a constant megaphone for the success that sellers are having in the market and be annoying about it. The more you can link yourself to success with sellers the more W’s you can stack up.

3️⃣ - Be the News!
You’re the expert so act like it. Your content should be “news” worthy. Use video to demonstrate your expertise and be the resource that people constantly turn to for real estate in your market. Create content about inventory, pricing, timing, market(s), etc. so that you become the trusted authority in your local community.

Now more than ever top producers are even getting more TV time on local news outlets because this is a big point of focus for most of the market.

Be the news.

4️⃣ - Recruit.
“There isn’t a problem that recruiting can’t solve” - @cheplaklive 

When inventory is tight or transaction volume is naturally lower, the number one way I’ve seen that you can grow is through the production of others. If you want your bottom line to grow in 2023, recruiting will be a key way that you will do it.

Give these key metrics 4-6 weeks to correct and your results will be game-changing.

1️⃣- Response Rate. Right now, I’m seeing an avg. rate of 58%, meaning that if you generated 100 leads, 58 of those people would be talking to you (even if it’s to tell you to eff off).
 
If your response rate is lower than 58%, there’s something in this messaging that isn’t provoking any form of response. 

Typically what I see is that the initial messages are too long & don’t ask any questions.

NOTE: Texting should be the dominant focus for lead response/conversion unless the prospect specifically tells you that they want to talk. 95% of your leads are going to want to text first. 

2️⃣&3️⃣ is a hybrid b/t your Qualification Rate & Appointment Rate.

Avg. Qual Rate: 17% (of 58%) 
Avg. Appt Rate: 40% (of 17%) 

If these numbers are ⬇️ than normal, it’s typically because of the way you are communicating with them in your text/emails/calls. You need to improve your written communication skills and also need to stop writing books in your text messages. 

Most people communicate in short-hand and emojis, but when talking to a customer, write pages in a text. You’re making the other person think/work too hard, and you’re losing people.
 
Most people in the industry are using disruptive forms of advertising right now (meaning the user was doing something else but saw your ads & opted in) which means you could very quickly lose them. 

Shorten up the way you’re talking to them in written form and ask really good (and intentional) questions that trigger a response. Give this a solid 3-4 weeks for results.

4️⃣- Conversion Rate. If you aren’t converting 50%, there’s something happening in the active conversations/meetings you’re taking that isn’t making an impact on the buyer/seller you’re meeting with. 

Find a coach, mentor, or sales trainer that can help you understand how to improve. This is the final piece to the puzzle when optimizing your follow-up systems & processes. 

When each of these numbers is dialed in, you will truly have a system you can add any lead source, & your business will grow. 🚀
